the BBC organised roadshows on WW1 at home: we participated in Stoke (I day: public attendance 1250) and Wolverhampton (2day: 11,00 public attendance).
The importance of the impact of the project was in re-balancing public and media perceptions that the war was just about the war front and to promote understanding of the diverse experiences of men, women and children; of different social classes; of different nationalities and ethnicities; and in different localities, of the home font and how it changed over time.</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>56ea939cebaa05.14024085</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Media (as a channel to the public)</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:url>http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/1cSGCxphvDxY0h5Vd7gnSGH/stories-by-bbc-radio-station</gtr:url><gtr:year>2014,2015,2016</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput></gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:impactSummaryOutput><gtr:description>To increase public knowledge about the diversity and extent of the WW1 home front and its inter-relationship with the war front. This in turn has contributed to the engagement of local communities with their past and with one another.</gtr:description><gtr:firstYearOfImpact>2014</gtr:firstYearOfImpact><gtr:id>9FADBA3E-76FC-47FD-9229-FBB0E3A50866</gtr:id><gtr:impactTypes><gtr:impactType>Cultural,Societal</gtr:impactType></gtr:impactTypes><gtr:outcomeId>56ea961238f8b0.70168924</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sector>Culture, Heritage, Museums and Collections</gtr:sector></gtr:impactSummaryOutput></gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>7C1B6D9F-3CD9-44F0-81F2-F30E597BF840</gtr:id><gtr:title>The Home Front in Britain</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/322a3c2ff98a3c6e7add50b72a2aa5b4"><gtr:id>32